details.description: Here at Waterbean Coffee, we always try to stay original and never follow the trends. In a time when most coffee shops focus on getting the customers in and out of their doors the quickest, we try to give them a place to relax, hold meetings, go over schoolwork, or just hang out with friends. We want to be more than just another coffee shop.

raw_data.description: Here at Waterbean Coffee, we always try to stay original and never follow the trends. In a time when most coffee shops focus on getting the customers in and out of their doors the quickest, we try to give them a place to relax, hold meetings, go over schoolwork, or just hang out with friends. We want to be more than just another coffee shop.

reviews_data.review_text: I tried the Paradise drink, which was so sweet I couldn’t finish it bc my teeth hurt. Either get half pumps of syrup or order an extra shot (or two) of espresso to bring it back to reality. The flavors were on point tho! My wife’s matcha tasted good too, and I don’t even like matcha. The place was clean, bright, quiet, and had reasonably soft chairs if you need a comfortable place to work. Love that nearly all the tables were 2-seaters to fit in more people with adequate personal space, but in the back room there is a large table with room for 8-10 chairs. Bc it’s separated from the front dining room by the order counter, it looks like a prime place to have an off-site meeting or just enjoy your coffee family-style.
I love Waterbean Coffee & all their locations.  The owners are down to earth & cool people.
Great place!
Very spacious, but most of all, the matcha 😫 I ordered a matcha with lavender brown sugar with vanilla and ube cold foam. Unbelievably good and yummy, definitely will be coming back
Amazing service amazing coffee, the place is incredibly clean, the staff is very knowledgeable of their inventory & how to make coffee. definitely need to stop by!

review_questions.Vegetarian offerings: Large vegetarian selection, Vegetarian menu or section

reviews_data.review_text: It’s early on a Sunday morning and after a short bike ride, I have found myself drinking cappuccino (in a porcelain mug) on the Waterbean’s rooftop terrace. SPLENDID

Nice new coffee shop in the neighborhood. This review is about customer service: Emmanuel is always so kind and welcoming and he is the reason I will return. My first visit was not pleasant with another barista as she was not welcoming when I was checking out the spot for the first time, she acted as though she was bothered and only spoke when spoken to and in one word responses, but Emmanuel has completely turned around the experience. He sets the standard of how barista service should be! Thank you and great job to Waterbean for having him be a great representation of your company!
I wanted to go for my coffee and I fell in love with the establishment. I promise to return and try more variety. Everything looks delicious.
I love this place. The PARADISE is everything!! The barista was so pleasant and welcoming. I will definitely be switching to Waterbean for my fix!!
Good drink and good service.
Happened to go on the grand opening. Cute space, lots of drink options, and I loved the gluten free pastry options!! Definitely going again.
welcome to Noda!
